channel.description:

ive tried testing the port again with my anti virus and my firewall turned OFF still no luck. My laptop is not directly connect too the router im on a wireless connection, would this change any of the steps above in the youtube video.

Does this have anything to do with Servers? If not your in the wrong section.

well actually when you think about yes it does, how the hell are you supposed too get people on your server if you cant portforward.
[/quote]

Find something called cmd, on your computer. Find your IP address in that file, and put that in your no-ip. Your IP address probably defaulted, in summary: Your IP address on no-ip should be the same when you get your cmd address. Otherwise I have no idea.[/quote]
